title: Terry Martin's Chip n' Seal Classic
Michigan State Road Rampage
course: Flat, exposed 4.4 mile loop on country roads near Dansville, MI. But flat doesn\'t necessarily mean boring--strong spring winds should help to ensure that the racing is hard and the pain level high. And that\'s not all: the loop includes 1.2 miles of dirt road, to keep things interesting and select for a worthy winner.
registration: Opens at 8:30 am. Entry fee is $13 per rider. All racers must show a valid collegiate license in order to race. One day licenses will be available.
notes: Because of the dirt section on this course, STURDY WHEELS AND TIRES are recommended. This is a “good quality” dirt road, and you can certainly ride standard road equipment, but you should probably save the carbon rims and ultralite tires for another day. Yellow line rule in effect at all times. If there is no yellow line, then you must stay on the right half of the road. Follow vehicles will be provided.
directions: Registration and parking will be at Dansville High School. From East Lansing/Okemos, take Grand River Ave/M43 to Meridian Rd. Go SOUTH on Meridian for about 11 miles until you reach M36. Turn LEFT to go EAST on M36. Drive on M36 for about 2.5 miles until you reach the small town of Dansville. Turn RIGHT onto Adams Street and follow that into the school. For an online map, see: http://tinyurl.com/3bqff2. Please note that WE WILL NOT BE STARTING OR STAGING THE RACES AT THE SCHOOL; the staging will be at the start/finish line approximately 1.5 miles away (see maps below). There is no place to park at the start/finish, so if you want to watch other races, ride your bike there.

address.street: 3003 S. State St., G250A Wolverine Tower

description:
Tour De Gaslight
Michigan State Criterium Championships
Sponsored by Jade Pig Ventures
course: Located in down town East Grand Rapids the course is 8/10ths mile & mostly flat with four left-hand turns & sweeping curves.
registration: All USCF rules apply.  USCF riders must show license or purchase either a one-day license or annual license to race.  One day license riders may only ride Category Five.  Promoter reserves right to adjust purse or combine events based on the number of riders, and adjust race distances and start times.  Field limit of 50 riders in Category Five, and 10 riders in all other races.  Fee to register for an additional race will be $20 an no late fee applies for that additional registration.  Registration opens at 8:30am & closes 30 minutes prior to the scheduled start time of each race.
notes:
Masters 45+ $400 in Prizes to 5 places
Masters 55+ $200 in prizes to 3 places
directions:
FROM THE WEST: I-96 to Cascade Rd exit 40A west. Go west through M37 (East Beltline) and turn left on Robinson at the next light Lakeside Dr.  At the stop sign turn left an then right into the parking ramp drive.
